Cell["\<\
Now frames become equivalents of axes. The motivation of axes/Frame \
interchange is the oppotunity to label the frame at the middle of the frame. \
This opportunity is not given to the axes specification which may only \
labeled at their extreme ends by their predefined function. But this is \
possible with using Text [ ] subroutine of the Graphics [ ] function. This \
will be shown at the later pages of this manuscript.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.766045742347128*^9, 3.766045924524029*^9}, {
   3.7660459817793117`*^9, 3.7660459915007563`*^9}, {3.766838704756999*^9, 
