   3.7668895765700035`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"4b540b84-a8eb-4241-aabe-\
4a86ad7bd9fa"],

Cell["\<\
Plots of functions having discontinuities with Mathematica, result with \
graphs where the asymptotes are not shown. To make them visible, we have to \
add some options.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7661694427715964`*^9, 3.7661695908440647`*^9}, {
  3.766311762388438*^9, 
  3.7663117832534914`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ef65b8b-6a91-4c36-8a86-\
d9c951ce5700"],

Cell["Plot[f, {x, a,b}, Exclusions \[Rule] {list}]", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7661696517262516`*^9, 
  3.766169720148403*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"839fae64-4578-4d6a-8ff3-\
b4bf7b160605"],

Cell["\<\
Mathematica, by default take  Exclusions \[Rule] All, to make them visible we \
should turn it to  Exclusions \[Rule] None\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7661698737447343`*^9, 3.766169898397112*^9}, {
  3.7661699499452095`*^9, 
