Cell["\<\
The neighborhood of a region where small changes of the independent variable \
result big changes of the dependent variable is the region of discontinuity \
of the function. From the graphical result, we conclude that the given \
function has a type 2 unremovable discontinuity at x = 1 . The plot also show \
that an asymptotic line exist at x = 0 . We will bring the vertical asymptote \
at light by adding the option, Exclusion \[Rule] None.  \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.766166483357724*^9, 3.766166549356555*^9}, {
   3.766166654906567*^9, 3.7661668989662666`*^9}, {3.766166935738049*^9, 
