Cell["\<\
At first sight, the function seems to be continious by its graph. But, this \
is not the case. We should not forget there is a single x in the denominator. \
When this x will be equal to zero in the range [-2 , 2] the function will \
have a discotinuity. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7664916824258485`*^9, 3.766491833202186*^9}, {
  3.7664919684182467`*^9, 3.766492009717484*^9}, {3.767020105729829*^9, 
  3.767020123485694*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e67b2ada-2c29-4186-bfba-\
9b82bd34bd23"],

Cell["\<\
From the plot of this function, we observe that the discontinuity is not a \
jump discontinuty, in contrary it is a point  discontinuty. This will imply \
also that if x will be near in both sides about \[Epsilon] (epsilon) the \
function will tend to its limit \[Delta] =1 in both side the value of the \
discontinuity without being equal to it. Then various types of discontiuties \
occur depending the structure of the function.This is first class A type \
removable discontinuity because the limits of both sides of the asymptotic \
line is real and equal to each other. This make this function piecewise, but \
contigious in -\[Epsilon] and + \[Epsilon] advances of the independent \
variable (x) before and after the point of discontinuity.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7664920191856017`*^9, 3.7664922563393784`*^9}, {
  3.7664922974348555`*^9, 3.766492485343051*^9}, {3.766492528578904*^9, 
  3.766492579530489*^9}, {3.766492637110301*^9, 3.766492709025653*^9}, {
  3.7664927688137617`*^9, 3.7664928322427077`*^9}, {3.766492878835554*^9, 
  3.766492936716176*^9}, {3.7670202064713316`*^9, 3.767020297439421*^9}, {
  3.767020328371772*^9, 
  3.7670204183754234`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d876cc2f-666c-468a-a515-\
cb18d165ec4c"],

Cell["\<\
This make the function piecewise but this stay unnoticed when inspecting the \
graph of the function. To understand the piecewise behavior of the function \
we will graph each piece separately :\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.766492517477697*^9, 3.7664925215421247`*^9}, {
   3.766492609939045*^9, 3.766492622386162*^9}, {3.766492958694175*^9, 
   3.7664930408782654`*^9}, 3.7664932602855535`*^9, {3.766493366606533*^9, 
   3.766493473837448*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d5412a50-3f35-4d21-9aa0-\
4c98dc860cc5"],

