Cell["\<\
That show that the given function has a second class nonremovable essential \
discontinuty. The graph of the function in this case is extremely important. \
The values of the function at the near vicinity of the asymptotic line \
tending to the different infinities is only observable from the plot of these \
functions. Also careful attempts to assess the values in the vicinities of \
the asymptotic line is also informative.\
\>", "Text",
